 xlink:href="IndianJOphthalmol-56-150-g003"/></fig><fig id="F4" position="float"><label>Figure 4</label><caption><p>The clinical photograph of the hands showing right hypoplastic (floating) right thumb</p></caption><alt-text>Figure 4</alt-text><graphic xlink:href="IndianJOphthalmol-56-150-g004"/></fig><fig id="F5" position="float"><label>Figure 5</label><caption><p>X-ray of the right hand shows small first metacarpal (like phalanx) with floating right thumb</p></caption><alt-text>Figure 5</alt-text><graphic xlink:href="IndianJOphthalmol-56-150-g005"/></fig></floats-group></article>